{"id":"b30dbc69-e7e7-4cec-af21-13cc6ba93e90","title":"SIP vs FD — कौन सा बेहतर है?","messages":[{"id":"1784133349680","role":"user","content":"SIP vs FD — कौन सा बेहतर है?"},{"id":"1784133349681","role":"assistant","content":"**💡 Quick Answer: SIP और FD दोनों में से बेहतर कौन सा है, यह आपकी financial goals, risk tolerance, और investment horizon पर depend करता है। Generally, SIP में higher returns की possibility होती है, लेकिन इसमें risk भी अधिक होता है।**\n\nSIP (Systematic Investment Plan) और FD (Fixed Deposit) दोनों ही popular investment options हैं, लेकिन इनमें कुछ fundamental differences हैं:\n\n### SIP vs FD: Key Differences\n1. **Risk Level**\n   - **SIP**: Higher risk क्योंकि यह market-linked है (equity or equity mutual funds में invest करता है)\n   - **FD**: Zero risk क्योंकि यह पूरी तरह से guaranteed है (bank या post office में deposit)\n\n2. **Returns Potential**\n   - **SIP**: Higher returns की possibility (historically ~12-15% returns दी हैं long-term में)\n   - **FD**: Lower लेकिन fixed returns (~7-8% p.a. currently)\n\n3. **Liquidity**\n   - **SIP**: Relatively liquid (exit कर सकते हैं but exit load या tax implications हो सकते हैं)\n   - **FD**: Premature withdrawal पर penalty लग सकता है (e.g., 0.5% to 1% loss)\n\n4. **Tax Implications**\n   - **SIP**: LTCG (Long Term Capital Gains) tax applicable अगर holding period >1 year है (tax rate: 10% without indexation)\n   - **FD**: TDS applicable अगर interest >₹40,000 (₹50,000 for senior citizens) और tax slab के according tax देना होता है\n\n### Example Comparison\nमान लीजिए आप **₹5,000/month** invest कर रहे हैं 10 साल के लिए:\n- **SIP** (at 12% returns): ~₹11.6 lakh बन सकते हैं\n- **FD** (at 7.5% interest): ~₹8.7 lakh maturity amount होगा\n\n```chart\n{\n  \"title\": \"SIP vs FD Returns (10 Years, ₹5,000/month)\",\n  \"type\": \"bar\",\n  \"yAxisFormatter\": \"currency\",\n  \"data\": [\n    {\"name\": \"SIP (12%)\", \"value\": 1160000},\n    {\"name\": \"FD (7.5%)\", \"value\": 870000}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 🎯 Key Takeaway\nSIP में higher returns की possibility है लेकिन इसमें market risk है। FD पूरी तरह से safe है लेकिन returns कम हैं।\n\n### अगला कदम (Next Step)\n1. अपनी risk tolerance assess करें।\n2. अपनी financial goals के according choose करें।\n3. SIP के लिए MoneyCal का **SIP Calculator** use करें: https://moneycal.in/tools/sip-calculator\n4. FD returns check करने के लिए **FD Calculator** use करें: https://moneycal.in/tools/fd-calculator\n\n⚠️ Disclaimer: यह financial advice नहीं है। Investment decisions लेने से पहले certified financial advisor से consult करें।","isStreaming":false,"sources":[{"title":"AMFI India","url":"https://www.amfiindia.com/","domain":"amfiindia.com"},{"title":"MoneyCal.in","url":"https://moneycal.in","domain":"moneycal.in"}],"recommendations":[{"id":"prepayment-calculator","title":"The Sovereign Wealth Optimizer (Loan Prepayment vs Investment)","description":"Elite Debt vs. Equity Analysis tool for FY 2026-27. Compare loan prepayment interest savings against mutual fund SIP wealth generation. Make the smartest debt decision for 2026.","category":"Loan Calculators","url":"/tools/prepayment-calculator","keywords":"The Sovereign Wealth Optimizer (Loan Prepayment vs Investment) Loan Calculators","type":"calculator"},{"id":"sip-calculator","title":"SIP Calculator","description":"Free SIP Calculator India – Systematic Investment Plan Calculator for mutual funds. Calculate SIP returns, maturity amount, and wealth creation with rupee cost averaging. Compare SIP vs lumpsum.","category":"Investment Calculators","url":"/tools/sip-calculator","keywords":"SIP Calculator Investment Calculators","type":"calculator"},{"id":"step-down-sip-calculator","title":"Step-Down SIP Calculator","description":"Model SIP with annual decrease. Plan tapered contributions near goals or pre-retirement while keeping compounding discipline.","category":"Investment Calculators","url":"/tools/step-down-sip-calculator","keywords":"Step-Down SIP Calculator Investment Calculators","type":"calculator"},{"id":"fd-calculator","title":"FD Calculator","description":"Free Fixed Deposit (FD) Calculator India. Calculate FD maturity, interest earned, and effective annual rate with monthly, quarterly, or annual compounding. Compare SBI, HDFC, ICICI rates.","category":"Investment Calculators","url":"/tools/fd-calculator","keywords":"FD Calculator Investment Calculators","type":"calculator"}],"followUpQuestions":["SIP में investing करते समय कौन से best practices follow करने चाहिए?","FD में premature withdrawal के क्या rules हैं?","SIP vs Lumpsum: कौन सा investment option बेहतर है?"]}],"createdAt":"2026-07-15T16:36:25.513Z","updatedAt":"2026-07-15T16:36:25.513Z"}